Adventures in OpenCL: Part 1
http://enja.org

Getting Started: building and running a minimalist kernel

Build:
you should first copy and edit the appropriate environment script for your system
../environment/setupenv_linux or ../environment/setupenv_mac
then source it:
source ../environment/setupenv_yourscript

next make a build directory and build the tutorial
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make

execute the example program
./part1.x

